---
/**
 * context-engineering 0001 · Figure 1 — the hero "same LLM, different context".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0001-what-is-context-and-context-as-query.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …). In an .astro file the SVG is plain HTML, so it
 * renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block at
 * the top of the document <body> (ids: arw, arwG, arwR, arwM). The MDX has no
 * such shared block, so the markers this figure references (arw, arwG, arwR) are
 * inlined into its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 300"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Two systems feed the same LLM; the curated one looks smart, the dumping one looks dumb."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <!-- System A -->
        <rect
            x="34"
            y="28"
            width="250"
            height="96"
            rx="10"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="159" y="48" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >System A — dump everything</text
        >
        <text x="159" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >whole repo · stale wiki · unrelated tickets</text
        >
        <text x="159" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >truncated to fit · signal buried in noise</text
        >
        <text x="159" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#9a2417"
            >"more context = better" (wrong)</text
        >
        <!-- System B -->
        <rect
            x="356"
            y="28"
            width="250"
            height="96"
            rx="10"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="481" y="48" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >System B — curate the few</text
        >
        <text x="481" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >the 3 right files · the current doc</text
        >
        <text x="481" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >the one rule that matters · nothing else</text
        >
        <text x="481" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >"right context, ruthlessly selected"</text
        >

        <!-- arrows into model -->
        <line x1="159" y1="124" x2="270" y2="166" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="481" y1="124" x2="370" y2="166" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- same model -->
        <rect
            x="230"
            y="168"
            width="180"
            height="50"
            rx="10"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="188" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Same LLM</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="205" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >identical weights · identical price</text
        >

        <!-- outputs -->
        <line x1="270" y1="218" x2="160" y2="252" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line x1="370" y1="218" x2="480" y2="252" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <rect x="40" y="254" width="230" height="34" rx="8" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="155" y="275" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >&#10007; vague · generic · confidently wrong</text
        >
        <rect x="370" y="254" width="230" height="34" rx="8" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="485" y="275" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >&#10003; precise · specific · correct</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The thesis of the whole track: the model is the constant. <b>Context is the variable.</b> "Smart
        vs dumb" is mostly an artifact of what got loaded into the window, not of which LLM you bought.<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
